full_text: Welcome to the segmentation demonstration. I enter Eileen Lang's username and password and click Login. Let's look at the Carrie Jones claim. Note that there are no exposures on this claim because it is an incident only claim. On the status page.  I see that the claim segment is, workers compensation, medical only. By way of comparison. Let's look at the Jim Anderson claim. Here, there are two exposures, one for medical details and one for indemnity. And, when I look at the status page. Because there is an indemnity exposure associated with the claim, this claim is segmented as workers comp, indemnity. There is a third segment, workers comp, employers liability. But because segmentation takes place during claim setup, and the new claim wizard in the base configuration does not provide an option to indicate employers liability, this segment will not ordinarily be used. However, claims with employers liability may enter the system from an external FNULL application, and the wizard can be configured to enable indicating employers liability. I logout as Eileen Lang. This concludes the demonstration of segmentation. segments.text: Welcome to the segmentation demonstration. I enter Eileen Lang's username and password and click Login. Let's look at the Carrie Jones claim. Note that there are no exposures on this claim because it is an incident only claim.
I see that the claim segment is, workers compensation, medical only.
Let's look at the Jim Anderson claim.
Here, there are two exposures, one for medical details and one for indemnity.
And, when I look at the status page.
Because there is an indemnity exposure associated with the claim, this claim is segmented as workers comp, indemnity.
There is a third segment, workers comp, employers liability.

But because segmentation takes place during claim setup, and the new claim wizard in the base configuration does not provide an option to indicate employers liability, this segment will not ordinarily be used.
However, claims with employers liability may enter the system from an external FNULL application, and the wizard can be configured to enable indicating employers liability.
This concludes the demonstration of segmentation.
